The tension with Lulu had caused Cody to take the right fork of the passageway, and he, figuring one direction was a good as another, continued along that branch. Lulu trotted along behind him, snarling to herself. “Don't worry, Lulu,” Cody reassured her. “I'm sure you'll have plenty of other animals – and humanoids, and perhaps the odd giant – to terrorize soon enough.”
